+{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1772769956463,"sessionID":"ses_33ead4776ffe9dpmkDXtJ99rw3","part":{"id":"prt_cc152cf63001QQeNV6XLu0HQQf","sessionID":"ses_33ead4776ffe9dpmkDXtJ99rw3","messageID":"msg_cc152cddb002xsM03u39Ub4h8E","type":"tool","callID":"e6a450022","tool":"write","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/workspace/.opencode/plans/ralph-plan.md","content":"# Plan for Versioned Document Store with Structural Merge\n\n## Original request\nBuild an in‑memory versioned document store (\"Git for JSON documents\"). Implement a `DocumentStore` class (or factory) with CRUD, version history, branching, and three‑way structural merging. Export it from `src/index.ts`. The library must be pure TypeScript, in‑memory, synchronous, with deep cloning to avoid mutation.\n\n## Clarifications\nNo user clarifications were needed; the requirements are fully specified in the prompt.\n\n## Goal\nA working TypeScript implementation that passes any hidden tests. The `DocumentStore` must:\n- Support create, get, update, delete on documents per branch.\n- Record versions with unique IDs, timestamps, full content.\n- Provide history and version lookup.\n- Allow branch creation, switching, listing.\n- Perform three‑way merges with conflict detection, returning a `MergeResult` as described.\n- Ensure deep cloning on storage/retrieval.\n- Keep all data in memory, no persistence.\n\n## Approach (step‑by‑step)\n1. **Define core types** (`Version`, `MergeResult`, `Conflict`).\n2. **Utility functions**:\n   - `deepClone<T>(obj: T): T` using `structuredClone` if available or JSON round‑trip.\n   - `isEqual(a, b): boolean` for primitive/JSON equality (deep compare).\n   - `getAllPaths(obj)`: generate dot‑separated paths for a JSON object.\n   - `getValueAtPath(obj, path)`, `setValueAtPath(obj, path, value)`.\n   - `threeWayMerge(base, ours, theirs)` returning `{ merged, conflicts }`.\n3. **Internal data structures**:\n   - `branches: Map<string, BranchState>` where `BranchState` holds `documents: Map<string, DocumentState>`.\n   - `DocumentState` holds `current: object | undefined` (undefined for deleted) and `versions: Version[]`.\n   - `branchParents: Map<string, string>` to track from which branch a branch was created (for ancestor lookup).\n   - `commitHistory: Map<string, Set<string>>` optional for finding common ancestor (simplify by storing snapshot of each branch's document versions at branch creation).\n   - Simpler approach: store for each branch a snapshot of document versions map; to find common ancestor we can walk up `branchParents` until a branch name matches (first common). Since branches are created from a specific branch, the divergence point is the branch where they split. We'll record `baseBranch` when creating a branch.\n4. **Implement CRUD**:\n   - `create` throws if document exists in current branch (`documents` map has non‑undefined entry).\n   - `update` throws if not exist; creates a new version (generate UUID via simple increment counter or timestamp+random). Store deep clone.\n   - `delete` marks document as undefined and records a version indicating deletion? Could store a special flag. Simpler: remove from map and add a version with `content: null` or keep `null`.\n5. **Version history**:\n   - `getHistory(id)` returns versions array (clone each version's content).\n   - `getVersion(id, versionId)` find version and return deep cloned content.\n6. **Branching**:\n   - Default branch \"main\" created on store initialization with empty state.\n   - `createBranch(name, fromBranch?)` copies the `documents` map (deep clone of each document's state) from source branch.\n   - `switchBranch(name)` sets `currentBranch`.\n   - `listBranches` returns keys of `branches`.\n7. **Merging**:\n   - Locate base branch: find common ancestor by walking parents of both branches until a match.\n   - For each document ID present in any of the three states, compute three‑way merge using utility.\n   - Build `merged` map of document IDs to merged content (deep clone).\n   - Collect conflicts.\n   - If `conflicts.length===0`, apply merged result to current branch's documents (replace current docs with merged). Set `applied:true`.\n   - Else `applied:false` and do not modify current branch.\n   - Return `MergeResult` with `merged` (showing ours-preferred for conflicts) and `conflicts`.\n8. **Export** the `DocumentStore` class.\n9. **Write tests** (not required, but hidden tests will run). Ensure public API matches interface.\n\n## Key files\n- `src/index.ts` (main implementation, may split into helper modules within src if desired).\n\n## Risks & Mitigations\n- **Ancestor detection**: branches can be created from non‑current branches; tracking parent lineage solves it.\n- **Deep clone performance**: using `structuredClone` (Node 17+) or fallback to `JSON.parse(JSON.stringify())`.\n- **Conflict detection**: need accurate path enumeration for nested objects and arrays. We'll treat arrays as values; if arrays differ, it's a conflict on the whole field.\n- **Version IDs uniqueness**: simple counter per store ensures uniqueness.\n- **Deletion handling**: treat missing document as `undefined`. During merge, if one side deletes and other modifies, that's a conflict.\n\n## Next steps\n1. Create progress log file with initial state.\n2. Implement helper utilities.\n3. Implement DocumentStore class with CRUD, versioning, branching.\n4. Implement merge logic.\n5. Run `npm test` (if tests exist) to verify.\n\n---\n**End of plan**","overwrite":true},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","title":".opencode/plans/ralph-plan.md","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/workspace/.opencode/plans/ralph-plan.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"time":{"start":1772769956450,"end":1772769956462}}}}
